# Training Plan Agent - Development Rules

## General Development Principles

### British English
- Use British English in all comments, documentation, and user-facing text
- Examples: "analyse" not "analyze", "optimise" not "optimize", "colour" not "color"

### Code Quality Standards
- Follow PEP 8 for Python code
- Use TypeScript strict mode for frontend
- Implement comprehensive error handling
- Write self-documenting code with clear variable names
- Add type hints to all Python functions

### Documentation
- Document all public APIs and functions
- Keep README.md updated with setup instructions
- Maintain architecture documentation
- Use docstrings for all classes and methods

## Development Process

### Pre-Development Requirements
1. **GitHub Issues**: All development must be tracked via GitHub issues
2. **Test-Driven Development (TDD)** approach for all features
3. **Code Review**: All code must be reviewed before merging
4. **Documentation**: Comprehensive documentation for all features
5. **Architecture Review**: Before any coding begins

### GitHub Issue Workflow
1. **Create Issue**: Every feature/bug starts with a GitHub issue
2. **Issue Template**: Use appropriate issue template (Feature, Bug, Documentation)
3. **Issue Description**: Clear description with acceptance criteria
4. **Issue Labels**: Use appropriate labels (enhancement, bug, documentation, etc.)
5. **Issue Assignment**: Assign to appropriate developer
6. **Issue Linking**: Link related issues and pull requests

### TDD Process (Red-Green-Refactor)
1. **Red**: Write failing test first
2. **Green**: Write minimal code to make test pass
3. **Refactor**: Clean up code while keeping tests green
4. **Repeat**: Continue cycle for each feature

### Virtual Environment Management
- Always create and use Python virtual environments
- Never install packages globally
- Document all dependencies in requirements.txt
- Use exact version pinning for production dependencies

### Testing Strategy
- Write unit tests for all business logic
- Implement integration tests for API endpoints
- Use pytest for Python testing
- Use Jest for frontend testing
- Maintain minimum 80% code coverage

### Code Review Process
- All code must be reviewed before merging
- Use meaningful commit messages
- Follow conventional commit format
- Include tests with every feature
- Link pull requests to GitHub issues
- Require approval before merging

## Project Structure Standards

### Backend (FastAPI)
```
backend/
├── app/
│   ├── models/          # Pydantic models
│   ├── services/       # Business logic
│   ├── repositories/   # Data access layer
│   ├── api/           # API endpoints
│   └── utils/         # Utilities and helpers
├── tests/             # Test files
├── requirements.txt   # Dependencies
└── .env.example      # Environment template
```

### Frontend (Next.js)
```
frontend/
├── src/
│   ├── app/           # Next.js app router
│   ├── components/    # Reusable components
│   ├── lib/          # Utilities and API clients
│   └── hooks/        # Custom React hooks
├── tests/            # Test files
└── package.json      # Dependencies
```

## Database and Data Management

### Repository Pattern
- Implement abstract repository interfaces
- Support PostgreSQL with Supabase
- Use dependency injection for data access
- Maintain database-agnostic design

### Data Validation
- Validate all input data with Pydantic
- Implement comprehensive error handling
- Use proper HTTP status codes
- Log all data operations for debugging

## API Design Standards

### RESTful Endpoints
- Use proper HTTP methods (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE)
- Implement consistent response formats
- Use proper status codes
- Include pagination for list endpoints

### Error Handling
- Return structured error responses
- Include error codes and messages
- Log errors for debugging
- Provide user-friendly error messages

## Security and Privacy

### Data Protection
- Encrypt sensitive data at rest
- Use HTTPS for all communications
- Implement proper authentication
- Follow GDPR principles for user data

### API Security
- Validate all inputs
- Implement rate limiting
- Use secure headers
- Log security events

## Performance Standards

### Backend Performance
- Use async/await for I/O operations
- Implement caching where appropriate
- Optimise database queries
- Monitor response times

### Frontend Performance
- Optimise bundle size
- Implement lazy loading
- Use proper image optimisation
- Monitor Core Web Vitals

## Voice Processing Standards

### Speech-to-Text
- Use OpenAI Whisper API for accuracy
- Implement fallback mechanisms
- Handle different accents and speech patterns
- Provide real-time feedback

### Data Extraction
- Parse exercise data accurately
- Handle various input formats
- Implement validation and correction
- Provide user confirmation

## LLM Integration Standards

### Context Management
- Build comprehensive user context
- Include training history and preferences
- Maintain conversation context
- Optimise prompt engineering

### Response Processing
- Validate LLM responses
- Implement fallback mechanisms
- Handle edge cases gracefully
- Provide explainable recommendations

## Mobile-First Design

### Responsive Design
- Design for mobile devices first
- Ensure touch-friendly interfaces
- Optimise for voice input
- Test on various screen sizes

### Voice Interface
- Design for hands-free operation
- Provide clear audio feedback
- Implement voice commands
